he alternative tags instead - so this introductory framing is actually important context that shouldn't be omitted. I'm weighing whether the omission of WriteTag being the standard method is actually critical or just contextual. The section title itself signals that users are specifically looking for non-escaped output, so they already know they want alternatives to the normal approach. The key decision—use PrettyPrintTag or RawWriteTag only when you need non-escaped HTML—is preserved in the knowledge file. I'll classify this as a minor omission since it's more navigational context than decision-critical information. I'm weighing whether the reference to WriteTag as the standard output method constitutes a meaningful omission. The source text does establish that WriteTag is the normal approach and the non-escaped alternatives are exceptions, but since this knowledge file section is specifically focused on non-escaped output scenarios, that contextual framing feels more like navigational reference than critical decision-making information. Given the checklist criteria about technology selection guidance, I'll flag it as a minor omission to be thorough. The introductory context for s6 is actually important—it establishes that WriteTag is the default choice for output with HTML escaping, and the alternatives like PrettyPrintTag or RawWriteTag should only be used when you specifically need unescaped HTML tags. Without this guidance, an AI might recommend the wrong tag for general use cases. So I'm marking this as having issues due to that missing context about when to use each option.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":23694,"cache_read_input_tokens":29873,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":23694,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"17234e78-35d4-46dc-a66a-cbf753933f61","uuid":"a676f980-a775-470b-9325-9